post_text:
Today is North Texas Giving Day! We invite our community to donate to the Terrell ISD Excellence Foundation! To-date, the Foundation has awarded over $1,000,000 in grant funding to our teachers, schools, and students. Grants have included but are not limited to STEAM equipment, technology in the classrooms, field trips and hands on learning experiencing, and educator trainings. TISD is incredibly grateful for the generosity and partnership of the Terrell ISD Excellence Foundation!

Give today at www.terrellexcellencefoundation.org/

post_text:
Tiger Fans,

Tickets for the Varsity Football Game Friday night are officially sold out. Due to seating limitations caused by Covid-19 social distancing, we were only able to offer a portion of the seats in Memorial Stadium. We know this is a disappointment to our families, but we hope you are able to still able to cheer on the Tigers via live stream from the link we posted earlier today (also available on our website www.terrellisd.org) or by enjoying the game from Film Alley (see post from earlier today for details).

The online ticket company we have worked with has assured us they are working through the technical issues on their end to provide a better buyer experience for our fans.

Thank you again for your patience and understanding as we navigate yet more uncharted territory! We look forward to a great Homecoming game tomorrow!

Go Tigers!

post_text:
Tiger fans, tickets to Friday's home game go on sale to the general public tomorrow at 9am. You will find the guidelines and link for ticket purchase at www.terrellisd.org/tickets. It is currently password protected, but at 9am tomorrow the password will be lifted. Please note that when you see the seating map, the areas are labeled as Endzone, Visitor, and Home. To get to the home side, you need to scroll to the bottom of the seating chart.

A few reminders about ticket purchases:

- All tickets must be purchased online. No tickets will be sold at the gate
- All ticket sales are final and non-refundable
- Tickets will all have an assigned seat and row. To ensure social distancing, you will be required to sit in the assigned seat as listed on your ticket
- Masks/face coverings are required at all times in Memorial Stadium unless you are eating/drinking

If you have ordering issues, please contact info@hometowntickets.com For best buying experience use Google Chrome, Firefox, or Safari as your browser. Do NOT use Internet Explorer, it is not compatible with Hometown Tickets.

post_text: When local sky light company, Solar Accessories, donated leftover plexiglass material to FMS teachers Danielle Jasmin and Michael Daigrepont, they enlisted the help of their former students, now Terrell High School robotics students, to turn it into something special. The students engineered and built plexiglass table dividers for multiple FMS classrooms to provide a safe way for students to learn and collaborate in the classroom. This is just one of the many ways in which we are seeing creativity and innovation thrive during these unprecedented times.
text: When local sky light company, Solar Accessories, donated leftover plexiglass material to FMS teachers Danielle Jasmin and Michael Daigrepont, they enlisted the help of their former students, now Terrell High School robotics students, to turn it into something special. The students engineered and built plexiglass table dividers for multiple FMS classrooms to provide a safe way for students to learn and collaborate in the classroom. This is just one of the many ways in which we are seeing creativity and innovation thrive during these unprecedented times.

post_text:
Grab & Go Curbside meals will be available for all Terrell ISD at-home learners beginning the first day of school. Please see the below details for how, when, and where to purchase and pick-up your meals.

Pickup will be available during first period lunches along the curb outside the dining room/cafeterias at the following campuses:

THS: 10:55AM
FMS: 10:53AM
JWL: 10:30AM
WES: 11:15AM
GWE: 10:30AM
WHB: 10:50AM

Parents will need to pay through Lunch Money Now (https://www.lunchmoneynow.com/lmnter/splash.php). All current meal prices and menu options can be found on our School Nutrition webpage at http://www.terrellisd.org/school-nutrition.

Parents may go to one campus to pick up all meals for the TISD students in your household. Student ID's are required for pickup. Students will receive a lunch and a breakfast for the following day.

Thank you to the TISD School Nutrition Department for making this happen for our families!

The week of the first day of school is finally here! We can hardly sleep knowing we will see all of our Tigers soon! For those returning face-to-face, we ask that you please familiarize yourself with the COVID-19 self-screening form. Click here to see the form: https://drive.google.com/file/d/15oV5R24ve7iN8kYYXu1ivrY7pkZmLLRN/view

post_text:
Tiger Family,

We want to extend a heartfelt THANK YOU to all of you for your kindness, patience, grace, and flexibility as we put the finishing touches on our Return to Learn plans. We know there have been adjustments to the plan and hiccups along the way, but we have been amazed and grateful for your continued support and encouragement. It is our greatest joy and honor to serve the students and families of Terrell ISD and we thank you for trusting us with your children!

We hope everyone enjoys their weekend and gets plenty of rest. T-minus 5 days, Tigers!

post_text:
TISD Family,

We are excited to announce that we have received details from Kaufman County surrounding a free COVID-19 testing opportunity on August 21 and August 22 at the Terrell Airport located at 400 British Flying School Blvd, Terrell, TX 75160.

Appointments are required for the testing and are filled on a first come, first served basis. Please follow the below steps to schedule an appointment:

1. Visit the following site: https://www.gogettested.com/
2. Click the green "Get Started" button
3. Fill out all of the information (when it asks if you have a group code or location, select "no")
4. When you get to the page for the dates, select either August 21 or August 22.
5. On the location page, select the Terrell Airport address then select your time on the following page

If and when more dates are available, we will communicate those to our TISD community.

This resource is available in 90 languages. For more details go to: https://www.211texas.org/211/

post_text:
Incoming 7th grade students for the 2020-2021 school year are required to either receive the Meningococcal (MCV4) and Tdap immunizations, or provide your school nurse a notarized copy of the immunizations exemption form (found at https://corequest.dshs.texas.gov/).

The Texas Department of State Health Services Public Health Region 2/3 is currently taking appointments for free immunizations in their clinic on Tuesdays. To schedule an appointment, please call (972)-551-8488.

If you have a student entering Pre-K that needs their updated 4-year-old vaccines, you can call the same number and make an appointment.

Please bring your past immunization documents with you to your appointment. For assistance, please email melody.stowe@terrellisd.org.

Currently, there is no change to the Texas law regarding these immunizations due to the COVID-19 pandemic, however if any changes or adjustments are made, we will communicate those with our families as soon as possible.

post_text:
Next up in our TISD Fri-YAY's is a shoutout to Ms. Ginger Lilley from J.W. Long Elementary for becoming a published author! Ms. Lilley's book, "Stubborn Stanley" can be found on Amazon.

“Stubborn Stanley” is a book about perseverance. About a character who practices at something until he’s great at it.

Ms. Lilley said it had taken her nearly 30 years to finish it and have it self-published. She decided to finish It to show her students to never give up; to follow their dreams and do what they love and have a passion for.

Way to go, Ms. Lilley!

#TISDFriYAY

post_text:
Tiger Family,

Many of our TISD families may be eligible for this great resource from the State of Texas. We have received word that the deadline has been extended to July 31, 2020 and that there is still funding available for families who apply.

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) provides eligible families with a one-time payment for each child who previously received free or reduced-price meals. P-EBT works the same way Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP) benefits do and will help families get the food they need during the current pandemic. P-EBT will be administered by the Texas Health and Human Services Commission, Texas Department of Agriculture and Texas Education Agency. The application for P-EBT will be open until July 31, 2020.

To learn more about the benefit or if your family qualifies please visit https://yourtexasbenefits.com/Learn/PEBT#

Enroll with Terrell ISD for the 2020-2021 school year online at www.terrellisd.org/enroll. Due to the extensive planning and scheduling that will be required to accommodate students across our three learning options, we are asking families to please complete enrollment by Friday, July 17.

Please click the following link to access a guide to creating and creating a Parent Portal account: https://bit.ly/3i0Fqgj

As the District receives updates and guidance on what an in-person return will look like, we will continue to communicate those to our community. We realize those details are important factors when making an enrollment selection. We will be working through questions surrounding the Return to Learn options and posting the answers in a FAQ document.

post_text:
Mientras planeamos que nuestros Terrell Tigers vuelvan al aprendizaje este otoño, TISD está trabajando para garantizar la seguridad, el bienestar y el continuo crecimiento académico de todos nuestros estudiantes. Nuestras encuestas a la comunidad y al personal reflejan que no todos se sienten cómodos con un regreso a la escuela de manera presencial. Debido a esto, TISD ofrece tres opciones de inscripción para nuestros estudiantes y familias. La inscripción para el año escolar 2020-2021 se abrirá el 22 de junio y proporcionará estas tres opciones.

Tenga en cuenta que a medida que planeamos el aprendizaje presencial, los lineamientos que el Distrito recibe de los gobiernos estatales y locales son fluidos y cambian con frecuencia. Como consecuencia, a medida que se realicen ajustes en los lineamientos, se ajustarán también nuestros planes en el Distrito.

post_text: The District has made a change to the 2020-2021 calendar to allow for the potential closure due to bad weather or COVID-19. The changes to the calendar are the bad weather/COVID-19 days added June 1-11. These days will ONLY be used in the event of a closure. If the District does not have any unexpected closures due to COVID or bad weather, the last day of school will still occur on May 27.

post_text:
As we plan for our Terrell Tigers to return to learn this fall, TISD is working to ensure the safety, well being, and continued academic growth of all our students. Our community and staff surveys reflect that not everyone is comfortable with a face-to-face return to school. Because of this, TISD is offering three enrollment options for our students and families. Enrollment for the 2020-2021 school year will open on June 22 and will reflect these three options.

Please note that as we plan for face-to-face learning the guidelines the District is receiving from the state and local governments are fluid and frequently changing. As adjustments are made in the guidelines, the District will adjust our plans accordingly.
text:
As we plan for our Terrell Tigers to return to learn this fall, TISD is working to ensure the safety, well being, and continued academic growth of all our students. Our community and staff surveys reflect that not everyone is comfortable with a face-to-face return to school. Because of this, TISD is offering three enrollment options for our students and families. Enrollment for the 2020-2021 school year will open on June 22 and will reflect these three options.

Please note that as we plan for face-to-face learning the guidelines the District is receiving from the state and local governments are fluid and frequently changing. As adjustments are made in the guidelines, the District will adjust our plans accordingly.

- Map of stadium depicting gate and seating area locations

- Honor Cords
- Senior edition of the Terrell Tribune
- Cap and gown for those who have not yet picked up

post_text:
Will you commit to completing the 2020 Census to shape the future of Terrell?

Responding to the census is not only your civic duty; it also affects the amount of funding your community receives, how your community plans for the future, and your representation in government.

Specifically, data from the 2020 Census is used to:

1. Ensure public services and funding for schools, hospitals, and fire departments.
2. Plan new homes and businesses and improve neighborhoods.
3. Determine how many seats your state is allocated in the House of Representatives.

Complete the 2020 Census today by visiting https://2020census.gov/

post_text:
Incoming 7th grade students for the 2020-2021 school year are required to either receive the Meningococcal (MCV4) and Tdap immunizations, or provide your school nurse a notarized copy of the immunizations exemption form (found at https://corequest.dshs.texas.gov/).

The Texas Department of State Health Services Public Health Region 2/3 is currently taking appointments for free immunizations in their clinic on Tuesdays. To schedule an appointment, please call (972)-551-8488.

If you have a student entering Pre-K that needs their updated 4-year-old vaccines, you can call the same number and make an appointment.

Please bring your past immunization documents with you to your appointment. For assistance, please email melody.stowe@terrellisd.org.

Currently, there is no change to the Texas law regarding these immunizations due to the COVID-19 pandemic, however if any changes or adjustments are made, we will communicate those with our families as soon as possible.

Please help us congratulate our 2019-2020 Teachers of the Year! Today, all of our Campus Teachers of the Year were honored with their plaques and the District announced our Elementary Teacher of the Year, Mrs. Brittany Bosak from J.W. Long Elementary and our Secondary Teacher of the Year Ms. Sarah Hinton from Furlough Middle School. All of these teachers are outstanding and inspiring educators and we incredibly proud of them.

A special thank you to American National Bank of Texas for donating iPads for our District winners, Ham Orchards for helping with the gift baskets, Two Guys Laser Engraving for the plaques, and to Platinum Ford for providing $1,000 service credit to our District winners.

post_text:
Drumroll please......

Our incredible School Nutrition and Transportation team members completed their final Meals on the Bus deliveries yesterday. Together they delivered a total of 242,421 meals to Terrell ISD families during the school closure. We cannot thank these men and women enough for their dedication and service to our students. We would also like to thank the staff members and nurses who volunteered their time to help with the deliveries and wellness checks. These frontline workers are our heroes!

Today is our Senior Celebration, who is ready?! We are so excited to celebrate our Class of 2020 tonight at 6pm beginning at the Terrell ExCEL and ending at Terrell High School! Seniors, please go over the attached guidelines and instructions.

Also, if you did NOT receive your senior yard sign, we will have those available for pick-up outside the Jamie Foxx Performing Arts Center near the TIGER letters and 2020 numbers.

We can't wait to see you!

post_text:
Friday, May 22 will be the last day for our Meals on the Bus deliveries. There will not be any meal service provided May 25-29 to allow our School Nutrition team time to enjoy the Memorial Day holiday and to clean and prep their kitchens for the TISD Summer Feeding Program. The TISD Summer Feeding Program will begin on Monday, June 1 and will run throughout the summer weeks Monday - Thursday.

The meals will be grab-and-go and will be available for pickup from 10am-2pm at Dr. Bruce Wood Elementary, J.W. Long Elementary, Gilbert Willie Sr. Elementary, and Herman Furlough Jr. Middle School. Children ages 1-18 are eligible to receive two meals per day as long as they are present to receive the meals, or a student photo ID is presented upon pickup.

No meal service will be provided July 6 - July 9, as the entire District is closed for the 4th of July holiday.

We would like to take this time to once again thank the incredible men and women who went above and beyond during the school closure to deliver tens of thousands of meals to our students. We are grateful for all they have done!

post_text: Returning to work, returning to school, and graduation planning! Your TISD team is working hard to execute these next steps as safely and responsibly as possible. Hear the latest from Dr. Warnock by watching the following video.
text: Returning to work, returning to school, and graduation planning! Your TISD team is working hard to execute these next steps as safely and responsibly as possible. Hear the latest from Dr. Warnock by watching the following video.

post_text:
Along with returning digital devices today, please also bring your child's library books to drop off in designated campus boxes along the sidewalk outside Furlough Middle School. Our Technology team will not be able to accept any books during the technology drop off, so please utilized the labeled boxes.

Library book drop-off will be held at the same time as the device return: 12pm - 6pm Monday, May 18 and Tuesday, May 19.

post_text:
If you received a digital device (chromebook or hotspot) following the school closure in March, please bring those devices and all related equipment like chargers and cases to ExCEL today or tomorrow from noon - 6pm. Please have your student's school ID or school ID number ready to give to our staff to smoothly process the return.

We will also have campus specific boxes lined up along the sidewalk at Furlough Middle School where you can return any library books your student has at home.

post_text:
Calling all chromebook and hotspots! The time has come for students to return their devices! Please plan to return your district devices on either Monday, May 18 or Tuesday, May 19 at ExCEL between the hours of 12pm and 6pm. Please bring all items that were distributed to your students including chromebooks, hotspots, chargers, and cases.
You will pull through the parking lot of ExCEL just as you did to check out the devices. You will not need to leave your car.

Only devices distributed after the COVID closure are to be returned during these two days. Devices deployed through HSA, GLA, and the Technology Lending Grant will be collected at a different time. Teachers will communicate directly with these students/families with details on when and how to return their devices.

Thank you so much!

post_text:
It's official, our Senior parade is on! Thanks to the City of Terrell, we have an approved route for our Senior Celebration Parade! The parade will take place on the date of the original THS Graduation, Friday, May 22. We invite all of our Seniors to decorate their vehicles and meet in the FMS/ExCEL parking lot at 5:30 p.m. Beginning at 6pm, our seniors will be escorted onto the parade route that will begin by leaving ExCEL and taking a right on Colquitt, a left on 9th St., a left on State St., and ending at Terrell High School. Friends, family, and community members are encouraged to line the route in their cars in celebration of our Class of 2020.

The District currently has the THS graduation ceremony scheduled for Friday June 12. As we receive updates from the Commissioner of Education we will keep our families informed. We are in the process of also determining a July and August date for graduation in the event the stay home order/social distancing guidelines have not been lifted by June.

post_text:
Our Terrell High School Student Council has earned recognition as a Texas Association of Student Councils (TASC) Sweepstakes Council, the highest honor a TASC council can achieve. Sweepstakes councils must first earn recognition as an Outstanding Student Council based on documentation of student council organization, specific project areas, participation in TASC programs, and an evaluation by your administrator. In addition, Sweepstakes Councils must earn recognition in the areas of Pride and Patriotism, Energy and Environment, and Drugs, Alcohol, Safety and Health. Finally, Sweepstakes councils must submit their accomplishments in School and Community Service. It takes passion, dedication, purpose, planning, and hard work to achieve this. Only exceptional councils earn this honor, and you set the bar to which other councils should aspire.

Congratulations to this outstanding group of student leaders!

post_text:
Today, Terrell ISD got to be a part of something very special! Dustin Marical, one of our THS Seniors, departed for Marine boot camp this afternoon. To give him a proper goodbye, his family and friends organized a surprise, socially distanced send-off. Since leaving today meant that he would miss graduation, THS Principal and former Army veteran, Jay Thompson, presented Dustin with his diploma prior to his departure. Superintendent Dr. Georgeanne Warnock, School Board President Dena Risinger, and several board members and teachers were also present to celebrate Dustin. Hand sanitizer was promptly distributed following the surprise diploma presentation!

Good luck in this next chapter of your life Dustin, and thank you for your service!

Seniors, we hear you loud and clear! We asked for your input, and you responded. TISD has officially delayed 2020 graduation to Friday, June 12 to allow our seniors the opportunity to walk the stage in front of their family, friends, and peers. You have worked incredibly hard and we want you to have the celebration you deserve. Weather permitting, graduation will be held at Terrell Memorial Stadium at 8pm. We are also working with our venue provider to delay prom. As updates become available, we will let you know.

Parents/families of seniors, we need your help! We are working on something special for our Class of 2020 to commemorate a historic senior year. If you are a parent/guardian/family member of a senior, please complete the following form by Friday, April 24. https://forms.gle/73MWUBP5ekfJ95wT8
text:
Seniors, we hear you loud and clear! We asked for your input, and you responded. TISD has officially delayed 2020 graduation to Friday, June 12 to allow our seniors the opportunity to walk the stage in front of their family, friends, and peers. You have worked incredibly hard and we want you to have the celebration you deserve. Weather permitting, graduation will be held at Terrell Memorial Stadium at 8pm. We are also working with our venue provider to delay prom. As updates become available, we will let you know.

post_text:
One of our teachers at the Global Leadership Academy, Abbie McEnturff, shared a poem she recently wrote. We are sure many of our teachers can relate to her words. #WeMissOurTigers

March crept by
So much has changed
The lives we all knew
Now rearranged

Our classrooms sit still
Frozen in time
No more wondering
Who will lead the line

Days are now filled
With toil and worry
Did I leave them well?
Or did I get in a hurry?

Projects are unfinished
Some things left behind
The school is now silent
We are teaching online

They are our kids
Our class, our team
Now we can’t see them
It seems like a dream

Who will teach them
What I haven’t taught
How will they know
If they’ve got it or not?

I am their teacher
They are my class
COVID-19
We will outlast.

post_text:
TISD is so grateful to our incredible community partners! The Terrell Share Center has been a longtime partner of the school district and has served the community of Terrell for decades! The Terrell Share Center plays a significant role in our Citywide Back to School Fair each year.

For families that need extra support during COVID-19 related shutdowns, the Terrell Share Center will provide your family with basic grocery needs. Please visit the Share Center located at 103 Jones St. on Wednesday between 9:00am-11:30am or Thursday between 9:00am-3:30pm to receive groceries for your family. Upon arrival please stay in your car and wait for a volunteer to load groceries into your vehicle.

If your family is in a position to help, The Share Center welcomes monetary donations, and is in need of donations such as shampoo, soap, toothpaste, toilet paper, paper towels, tissue, and items for children's lunches.

We are in this together Terrell, and together we are stronger! #TerrellProud #TISDFriYAY

post_text:
Talk about the ultimate Fri-YAY! Starbucks shared our story of Terrell High School graduate, Alejandro, changing one of our employees flat tires in their parking lot! He not only changed her tire, but took her order while he changed it. Also, for those wondering, she ordered a Grande Flat White 🤣

Keep doing good Tiger Family! We are all in this together!
shared_text:
Starbucks
March 27 at 4:31 PM ·

Our partners (employees) create heart-warming connections with our customers every day, and when we heard this story we knew we had to share. 💚

This week, Alejandro saw a customer pull into the Drive-Thru with a flat tire and ran out to assist. He even stopped to take her order.

"The thing with doing good deeds is that it seems to have a trickle effect," says Alejandro. "If you help someone, even for a moment, it can influence how the rest of their day goes, and then when they interact with people, those conversations will be better. It’s a whole butterfly effect.”

In times like these, it's more important than ever to be kind and take care of each other. We're proud to be your partner, Alejandro. (Photo credit: Olivia R.)

Following Kaufman County's Shelter in Place announcement, TISD has extended the District closure through Monday, April 13, with the earliest possible return on April 14. The District continues to monitor the situation and will update families on any further extensions of closure.

Después del anuncio de Shelter in Place del Condado de Kaufman, TISD ha extendido el cierre del Distrito hasta el lunes 13 de abril, con el regreso más temprano posible el martes 14 de abril. El Distrito continúa monitoreando la situación y actualizará a las familias sobre cualquier otra extensión del cierre.

post_text:
Por favor, no ignore nuestra llamada! Todos los padres de TISD recibirán una llamada hoy del maestro de su hijo. Esta llamada es esencial ya que haremos un inventario de las necesidades de nuestros estudiantes y familias a medida que hacemos la transición al aprendizaje en el hogar. Si no puede contestar la llamada, se realizará un segundo intento. Si aún no podemos comunicarnos con usted, se enviará un correo electrónico al correo electrónico que tenemos en el archivo en el Portal de Padres.

Si las familias requieren una llamada en español, uno de los miembros de nuestro equipo bilingüe se comunicará con usted en breve.

¡Esperamos poder hablar con usted!

post_text:
Please don't ignore our call! All TISD parents will receive a call tomorrow from their child's teacher. This call is essential as we take inventory of the needs of our students and families as we transition to at-home learning. If you are unable to answer the call, a second attempt will be made. If we are still unable to get ahold of you, an email will be sent to the email we have on file in Parent Portal.

If families require a call in Spanish, one of our bilingual team members will get back in touch with you shortly!

We look forward to talking with you!

post_text:
Our principals and administrators are also participating in some at-home virtual learning! Staff members across the District this week are conducting meetings via Google hangouts!

In all honesty, it's easy to be discouraged given the current hand we have been dealt, but our team is only full of optimism! Our teachers are up to the challenge, our parents are patient and full of grace, and our students are bright and adaptable! We have never had as many tools at our fingertips than we do right now. It won't be without its challenges, but rest assured that our teams are building plans and strategies to make this transition to at-home learning as easy as possible!

We appreciate all of the heartfelt comments, messages, and emails! Thank you Tiger Family for your continued support and encouragement! #TerrellProud #TigerStrong

Great job students!

post_text:
At the Texas Association of Student Council’s regional Spring conference, Terrell High School’s Student Council was awarded the highest level of performance, being recognized as a “Sweepstakes” council. In order to obtain this status THS STUCO achieved “Outstanding” level in all four reporting areas: Pride and Patriotism, Energy and Environment, Drug Awareness, Safety and Health, and Overall Student Council, in addition to an acknowledgment of fine Community Service.

STUCO Sponsor and THS teacher John Bonadurer shared his excitement and pride regarding his students' achievements.

"This is truly a recognition of the hard work and dedication of the student council members and a distinction which they have now accomplished for a second year in a row."

Congratulations STUCO!

Did you know that public schools educate 9 out of every ten students across the nation? The public school system serves nearly 51 million students and is made up of 3.2 million teachers and hundreds of thousands of specialists, administrators, and support staff. Chances are, if you are reading this, public education has made a significant impact in your life!

Help us celebrate Public Schools Weeks by posting your pictures or sharing a few words about the positive influence public education has made on your life! Use #PublicSchoolProud and #TISDLovesPublicSchools

post_text:
Do you have a college bound senior? We understand getting ready for college can be stressful, and we want to help! The THS counselors are working hard to compile a list of as many scholarship opportunities as possible. Many of these are local scholarships, which means your student’s chances of receiving them are very high! However, if students do not apply, the foundations and businesses providing them may consider discontinuing the scholarships.

Please encourage your student to visit http://www.terrellisd.org/ths-scholarships to explore the national, state, and local scholarship opportunities. This list of scholarships is growing each week as the counselors add more opportunities, so check back often! Also be sure to keep an eye out for more reminders on Remind from the THS counselor, Charline Hoevers. Join her Remind list by texting @thstiger20 to the phone number 81010.

post_text: Our band students continue to impress! Click the image below to read the full article!
shared_text:
TERRELLTIGERNEWS.WEEBLY.COM
Tiger Band Earns 23 First Division Ratings at UIL Contest

Terrell ISD Fine Arts
February 7 at 8:29 PM ·

Terrell ISD Feature Story: Tiger Band Earns 23 First Division Ratings at UIL Contest

The Terrell High School Tiger Band competed at the UIL Region 3 Solo and Ensemble competition on Saturday, February 1 at North Garland High School. Over 2,500 high school students from Region 3 were in attendance. Out of the 28 Terrell High School students who attended the event, 23 received first division awards and six second division awards.

John Young, Director of Bands and Fine Arts commented, “this is an excellent start to having our band students continue striving for high expectations in their musicianship.”

Participating in the UIL Solo and Ensemble contest demands a lot of work and commitment from the student musicians and involves extra out of class practice and collaboration with the directors. Many of the solos are college level and require great dedication and musical expertise.

Click below to read the full article.

Tiger Family,

Terrell ISD is aware of the possibility of winter weather late tonight and early tomorrow morning. Student and staff safety remains our top priority, and we will therefore be closely monitoring the forecast, road conditions, as well as local media outlets. We will keep our families informed as updates become available and communicate any school delays or closures via Remind, the TISD website, Facebook, automated calls, and local news stations. Please note that this is a NOT a notice of a school closure or delay. School will take place as scheduled unless the District communicates otherwise.

We thank you for allowing us to serve your families! #SafeTigers #TerrellISD

post_text:
Terrell ISD Feature Story: Terrell High School UIL Teams Bring Home Medals from Mabank

Terrell High School’s UIL Academics, Speech, and Debate teams traveled to Mabank last weekend to compete in a 19-team meet. Terrell had strong performances in many areas with multiple students bringing home medals. The medal winners were John Ory, sixth in Number Sense, Tijana Krivokapic, sixth in LD Debate, Cash Muel, sixth in Computer Science, and Leilani Guzman, fifth in Computer Science. The Number Sense and Spelling teams took third place, and the Computer Science team took second place. While everyone performed exceptionally well at the meet, the top performance was Christian Baca in the Lincoln Douglas Debate, winning all three rounds of the debate competition and taking home first place.

Click the link below to read the full story.

While everyone performed exceptionally well at the meet, the top performance was Christian Baca in the Lincoln Douglas Debate, winning all three rounds of the debate competition and taking home first place.

post_text: This summer, Danceline Elite taught the annual Terrell Tigerette summer camp. During this week of camp, the girls learn their field routines and other routines for the upcoming year. Don’Yel Gordon, 2020-2021 Tigerette Captain and Natalie Arbogast, 2020-2021 First Lieutenant were both chosen by Danceline representatives for their outstanding dance and leadership abilities to travel to New York during the Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. weekend. The girls will attend a Broadway play, dance at the Famous Alvin Ailey American Dance Theatre and the Broadway Dance Center along with other dancers chosen from dance teams across the state. They will tour the Radio City Music Hall, Times Square, Central Park, The Statue of Liberty and Rockerfeller Center. Job well done girls!

Tiger Family,

To ensure student and staff safety, our team has been monitoring today's weather forecast and in communication with the Kaufman County Emergency Department. With the possibility of extreme weather entering our area later today, all evening activities have been cancelled. Campuses will dismiss at regular times, however we encourage parents of walkers to please make alternative arrangements for your students. Additionally, if your student is transported to an after school daycare, please connect with your childcare providers, as some facilities are closing early. We thank you very much and encourage all of our families to stay safe!

post_text:
The THS Students of the Chick-Fil-A Leader Academy made a difference this holiday season through “Do Good December” Service Project. The students divided into 3 teams DO, DRIVE and DELIVER.

Group DO created 50 care packages donated by Coach Mason and the THS boys Varsity Basketball team. Group DELIVER delivered the packages to Country View Nursing and Rehab center here in Terrell. Group DRIVE hosted a coats and blankets drive and collected over 100 warm items to be donated to the Homeless.

THS teacher and PALS Sponsor Veronica Johnson coordinated the efforts and events for the group. She shares "The students were really able to put servant leadership into action and serve our community!"

Thank you to this incredible group of students and staff for giving back to the community this holiday season.

Just a reminder to be sure to register your aspiring Terrell Tigerettes for the Jingle Bell Jam Mini Dance Camp on December 14 following the Christmas parade from 12:30-2:30 p.m at the Tigerette Gym at Terrell High School.

The mini camp is open to students Kindergarten-Fifth grade and costs $25 per student ($40 for two students in the same family). Camp will include dance choreography as well as a craft and t-shirt.

The Tiny Tigerettes will perform at a varsity basketball game on Monday, December 16. Email sharon.harper@terrellisd.org with your child's t-shirt size. Students are welcome to register on-site or with a Tigerette.

Terrell ISD Feature Story: Terrell ISD Names Alexis Dennis as Principal of Gilbert Willie, Sr. Elementary School

Terrell Independent School District is excited to announce Alexis Dennis as the new Gilbert Willie, Sr. Elementary Principal. Dennis joins the District from Carrollton-Farmers Branch ISD, where she has served as the Assistant Principal for Dave Blair Elementary School since 2016.

“The District is thrilled to welcome Mrs. Dennis to the Tiger family,” said Dr. Bruce Wood, TISD Interim Superintendent. “She has a proven track record of success, and I am confident she will bring a wealth of knowledge and experience to the GWE campus and staff.”

Click the link below to read the full story.

post_text:
It has been brought to the District's attention that several local businesses have been approached by a third-party marketing company to provide merchandise sponsorships in partnership with the THS Cheer or Drill team. Please be aware that this company has no official affiliation with the school district. We would caution anyone against doing business with any third party company claiming to be working on behalf of our schools, as none of the sponsorship efforts are benefiting any District programs. The District values the support of our Terrell businesses and organizations, and we work hard to protect the trust and relationships we have built within our community.

Unfortunately, these kinds of companies are targeting local business under the guise of district partnerships across the state, and ISD's are taking precautions to protect their local businesses. If there is ever need to verify the authenticity of a school district fundraiser or sponsorship, please contact Olivia Rice, Terrell ISD Director of Communications and Marketing at olivia.rice@terrellisd.org.
